# 1. Introduction

This document defines the overall testing strategy for the OrangeHRM Demo Application.

The objective is to establish a structured testing approach that ensures the application functions correctly, meets business requirements, and is ready for production deployment.

---

# 2. Purpose

The purpose of this Test Strategy is to:

- Define the testing approach
- Identify testing scope
- Define testing objectives
- Establish quality standards
- Ensure complete requirement coverage
- Reduce production defects

---

# 3. Scope

## In Scope

- Login
- Logout
- Dashboard
- Employee Management
- User Management
- Leave Management
- Recruitment
- Search Functionality

## Out of Scope

- Performance Testing
- Security Testing
- Mobile Testing
- Accessibility Testing
- Localization Testing

---

# 4. Testing Objectives

The testing objectives are:

- Verify application functionality.
- Validate business requirements.
- Identify defects early.
- Ensure system stability.
- Support successful User Acceptance Testing (UAT).
- Improve release confidence.

---

# 5. Test Levels

| Test Level | Objective |
|------------|-----------|
| Smoke Testing | Verify build stability |
| Functional Testing | Validate business functionality |
| Integration Testing | Verify module interactions |
| Regression Testing | Ensure existing functionality remains unaffected |
| User Acceptance Testing | Validate business workflows |

---

# 6. Test Types

The following testing techniques will be used:

- Functional Testing
- Positive Testing
- Negative Testing
- Boundary Value Analysis
- Exploratory Testing
- Usability Testing

---

# 7. Test Approach

The testing process follows the Software Testing Life Cycle (STLC).

```text
Requirement Analysis
        ↓
Test Planning
        ↓
Test Scenario Design
        ↓
Test Case Design
        ↓
Test Data Preparation
        ↓
Environment Validation
        ↓
Smoke Testing
        ↓
Functional Testing
        ↓
Defect Reporting
        ↓
Regression Testing
        ↓
UAT Support
        ↓
Test Closure
```

Testing will follow a **Risk-Based Testing** approach, prioritizing business-critical modules such as Login, Employee Management, and Leave Management.

---

# 8. Test Environment

| Item | Details |
|------|---------|
| Application | OrangeHRM Demo |
| Browser | Google Chrome (Latest) |
| Operating System | Windows 11 |
| Test Data | Demo Users |
| Test Repository | GitHub |
| API Tool | Postman |

---

# 9. Entry Criteria

Testing will begin only when:

- Requirements are approved.
- Test environment is available.
- Application build is deployed.
- Test data is prepared.
- Test cases are reviewed.

---

# 10. Exit Criteria

Testing will be considered complete when:

- All planned test cases have been executed.
- No Critical defects remain open.
- High-priority defects are resolved or accepted.
- Regression testing is completed.
- Test Summary Report is approved.

---

# 11. Defect Management

## Defect Lifecycle

```text
New
 ↓
Assigned
 ↓
In Progress
 ↓
Fixed
 ↓
Ready for Retest
 ↓
Closed
```

## Severity Levels

| Severity | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| Critical | Application unusable |
| High | Major functionality impacted |
| Medium | Partial functionality impacted |
| Low | Cosmetic or minor issue |

## Priority Levels

| Priority | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| High | Immediate fix required |
| Medium | Fix before release |
| Low | Can be fixed later |

---

# 12. Risks & Mitigation

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|------------|
| Requirement Changes | High | Review requirements regularly |
| Test Environment Issues | Medium | Validate environment before testing |
| Limited Test Data | Medium | Prepare representative test data |
| Delayed Defect Fixes | High | Daily defect review meetings |

---

# 13. Roles & Responsibilities

| Role | Responsibility |
|------|----------------|
| Business Analyst | Requirement clarification |
| QA Engineer | Test planning, execution, and reporting |
| Developer | Defect fixing |
| Project Manager | Project coordination |
| Client/UAT Team | Business validation |

---

# 14. Deliverables

The following documents will be produced during the testing lifecycle:

- Test Strategy
- Test Plan
- Test Scenarios
- Test Cases
- Requirements Traceability Matrix (RTM)
- Test Data
- Defect Report
- Test Summary Report
- Release Recommendation

